{
  "texts": [
    "Based the roles and environment, agents make actions to response users' or other agents' request.",
    "The actions can be made based on self-knowledge or tools that designed for domain-specific tasks.",
    "The request and the actions are stored in memory to support the future requests.In the current agents, the roles are typically assigned by prompts; however, prompt may cannot give a comprehensive discription of the role when the role is complex and the number of related data is large.",
    "Assiging roles with LoRA modules training from data related to the roles can be a better choice.",
    "Furthermore, the tools for agent can be LoRA modules."
  ]
}